{"uri":"bodo-saltans-ssu-gfp-neo-cassette-s5meg46","version_id":"0","protocol_name":"Bodo saltans SSU-GFP-Neo cassette","protocol_name_html":"Bodo saltans&nbsp;SSU-GFP-Neo cassette","is_prepublished":"0","can_edit":"0","parent_id":null,"api_version":"1","is_new_mode":"0","last_modified":"1535637539","type_id":"4","link":null,"fork_id":"","public_fork_note":"","number_of_steps":"0","has_versions":"0","first_published_date":"1535637539","publish_date":"2018-08-30 13:58:59","documents":"[{\"url\":\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/6k7d3an.seq\",\"file_id\":\"29021\",\"thumb_url\":\"\/img\/extensions\/file.png\",\"ofn\":\"SSU-GFP-Neo-SSU cassette_final.seq\"},{\"url\":\"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/6k8d3an.pdf\",\"file_id\":\"29022\",\"thumb_url\":\"\/img\/extensions\/pdf.png\",\"ofn\":\"18S-GFP cassette.pdf\"}]","have_protocol_in_step":"0","is_protocol_in_step":"0","vendor_name":"Contributed by users","vendor_link":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io","vendor_logo":"\/img\/vendors\/1.png","mod_mins":"4","mod_secs":"52","description":"<p>This plasmid is designed to integrate within the small subunit ribosomal RNA gene region of <em>B. saltans<\/em>. It carries 1 kb of the <em>B. saltans<\/em> small subunit ribosomal RNA gene. To construct this cassette, we first sequenced the complete ribosomal operon of <em>B. saltans<\/em>, which has a total length of \u00a0\u00a0\u03349 kb. The structure of the ribosomal operon of <em>B. saltans<\/em> is similar in the closely related kinetoplastida <em>Leishmania<\/em>, where the ribosomal RNA genes are arranged in head- to-tail repeats (Figure 4b and Yan et al.,\u00a0<em>Molecular and biochemical parasitology<\/em>\u00a0103, no. 2 (1999): 197-210). For the cassette construction, we used only a 1 kb region of the 18S ribosomal RNA gene, which is represented in the schematic as Homologous Recombination Region 1 (HR1) and Homologous Recombination Region 2 (HR2) each, of which is 500 bp . The GFP and Neo genes are located in the middle of the construct and their expression is controlled by the presence of the <em>B. saltans<\/em> tubulin intergenic region (Bs TUB IGR) at the 3\u2019 and 5\u2019 ends of each gene. As the transcription in <em>B. saltans<\/em> is polycistronic, the presence of the tubulin intergenic region is necessary for trans-splicing and polyadenylation. \u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>\n<p>\u00a0<\/p>","is_bookmarked":"0","can_reassign":"1","before_start":null,"has_guidelines":"0","materials":[],"warning":null,"version_class":"15245","public":"1","is_owner":"1","is_original_owner":"1","created_on":"1535636749","protocol_affiliation":"Harvard University,Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution,University of Georgia","affiliation":null,"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.s5meg46","doi_status":"2","changed_fork_steps":null,"profile_url":"w2y27433y2","protocol_img":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_document.png","profile_image":"\/img\/avatars\/017.png","full_name":"Fatma Gomaa","created_by":"Fatma Gomaa","private_link":"8DFFF44E7F78E70B036937B718A7CD32","original_img":"1","username":"fatma-gomaa","is_retracted":"0","retraction_reason":null,"plos_id":null,"manuscript_citation":null,"journal_name":null,"is_donations_disabled":"0","is_donations_disabled_by_user":"9","item_record_id":350052,"fork_info":[],"compare_forks":[],"protocols":[],"groups":[{"group_id":"108","group_uri":"protg","group_name":"Protist Research to Optimize Tools in Genetics (PROT-G)","group_logo":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/e3addmn.png","requested_uid":null,"request_flag":null,"my_request":"0"}],"number_of_shared_runs":[],"ownership_history":[],"keywords":"","transfer_to_user":[],"sub_transfer":false,"is_transfer_pending":false,"number_of_bookmarks":"0","collections":[],"tags":[],"archived":0,"sub_authors":[],"sub_protocols_number":0,"can_edit_shared":0,"shared_runs":[],"is_shared_run":0,"is_shared":1,"banner":null,"contact_badges":[{"badge_id":"4","badge_image":"\/img\/badges\/gold.sv